Privacy Policy

Introduction
BoomZone is a simple Minesweeper game built by ahmedabdelrahman4999@gmail.com. This game is provided for free and is intended for use as is.

This Privacy Policy is here to inform you that BoomZone does not collect, store, or use any personal information from users. The game is designed to provide a fun and simple experience without accessing any personal data.

Information Collection and Use
BoomZone does not collect any personally identifiable information, such as names, email addresses, or location data. The game operates fully offline and does not require an internet connection or access to any device permissions.

Cookies
BoomZone does not use any cookies or tracking technologies.

Third-Party Services
Since BoomZone does not collect any data, no third-party services are used for data collection, analytics, or advertising purposes.

Security
While BoomZone does not collect any data, we still prioritize delivering a safe and secure gaming experience. Please be aware that no data transmission over the internet or electronic storage is entirely secure, though this game does not transmit data.

Childrenâ€™s Privacy
BoomZone does not knowingly collect any personal information from anyone, including children under the age of 13. Since no data collection occurs, it is safe for all users.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
Although BoomZone does not collect or use any personal information, we may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and they will be effective immediately upon being posted.

